version_description: Inserted som missing chords in the verses according to the acoustic version of the song which suits better with a companing mandolin. Changed the tuning from the original E to G for us tenors...
It's an easier version that is in the same key as the original and has simple chords that still sound pretty good.
Just put the cords in using capo.
This includes the intro tabs and chord variations picked up from watching a live rendition.
I find this song easier to play when tuned down half a step. Listen to the song for timing. Hope it might help someone else.
This version of the song comes as a complete chord sheet including all parts and lyrics.
Capo at the first fret and play with your choice of power chords or open chords.
